    {
      "id": "https://www.strangerfoods.org/recipes/yogurtlu-kebap-with-hot-spiced-butter",
      "url": "https://www.strangerfoods.org/recipes/yogurtlu-kebap-with-hot-spiced-butter",
      "title": "Yogurtlu kebap with hot spiced butter",
      "content_html": "<h1 style=\"text-align:center;font-family:sans-serif;\">Yogurtlu kebap with hot spiced butter</h1>\n        <br>\n        <img src=\"https://www.strangerfoods.org/images/yogurtlu-kebap-with-hot-spiced-butter.webp\" style=\"text-align:center;\"/>\n        <br>\n        <p style=\"font-family:sans-serif;>From the Iskender kebabs of Bursa to the Beyti kebabs of Istanbul, there are a whole variety of fabulous Turkish kebabs to choose from. But here we have one of our favourites - yogurtlu kofte kebap! These kebabs consist of fried pitta bread topped with juicy lamb kofta, a simple tomato sauce, a drizzle of yoghurt and finely hot spiced butter on top. It's a rich and delicious combination served with a simple salad and some chips or rice on the side. </p>",
      "image": "https://www.strangerfoods.org/images/yogurtlu-kebap-with-hot-spiced-butter.webp",
      "date_published": "2026-03-08T00:00:00+00:00Z",
      "language": "en"
    },
